1. Preemptive Scheduling
CPU can be taken away from a process.

Example:
Round Robin
Priority (preemptive)

Advantage:
✔ Better response time

Disadvantage:
✘ Context switching overhead

2. Non-Preemptive Scheduling
CPU is not taken away until process finishes.

Example:
FCFS
SJF (non-preemptive)

Advantage:
✔ Simple implementation

Disadvantage:
✘ Poor response time
